Footballer Christian Atsu has been found dead under the rubble of his home almost two weeks after the Turkey earthquake, his agent has confirmed. The former Premier League footballer, who played for both Newcastle United and Chelsea, went missing following the devastating earthquake in Turkey and Syria on February 6. At least 25,000 people have died in southern Turkey and northern Syria since the earthquake and aftershocks that followed. More than 45,000 people have been killed in the earthquake.